WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.400 --> 00:00:15.176
Welcome to the MITRE tutorial. This view organizes current findings by ATT and CK tactics and techniques. A mapping is classification context, not proof that the full technique occurred.

2
00:00:16.576 --> 00:00:26.680
We load the sanitized SSH sample. Its rules map password guessing, valid accounts, and local account creation into one possible progression.

3
00:00:28.080 --> 00:00:36.816
Technique cards show the identifier, name, maximum severity, contributing rules, and evidence coverage under each attacker objective.

4
00:00:38.216 --> 00:00:49.976
For example, T eleven ten point zero zero one represents password guessing. Its evidence count comes from the current rule matches, not from an external threat-intelligence verdict.

5
00:00:51.376 --> 00:01:01.120
We click a short finding identifier to select the detection that created this mapping. Findings and Evidence preserve that selection for validation.

6
00:01:02.520 --> 00:01:11.280
Use the map to structure investigation language, then verify every label against rule logic and raw evidence before describing an attack chain.
